HEADWORD: Sacchulmin
<hw>Sac*chul"min</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>An amorphous huminlike substance resembling sacchulmic acid, and
produced together with it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

